                <head>270. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>According to <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Record of Action No. 2381, taken
                    at the 474th meeting of the National Security Council on January 18, 1961, the
                    National Security Council “Adopted the draft statement of policy on the subject
                    contained in <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 6028 [‘U.S. Policy Toward the
                    Horn of Africa’].” The Record of Action also indicates: “<hi rend="italic"
                        >Note</hi>: <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 6028, as adopted above,
                    subsequently approved by the President for implementation by all Executive
                    departments and agencies of the U.S. Government, and referred to the Operations
                    Coordinating Board as the coordinating agency.” (Department of State, <gloss
                        target="#t_SS1">S/S</gloss>-<gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    (Miscellaneous) Files: Lot 66 D 95, Records of Action) For text of <gloss
                        target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 6028, December 30, 1960, see <ref
                        target="frus1958-60v14#pg_197">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1958–1960, volume XIV, pages
                        197</ref>–<ref target="frus1958-60v14#pg_210">210</ref>.</p>
                <p>On the recommendation of Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_RD3"
                        >Rusk</persName>, President <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName>
                    authorized the recission of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> 6028 on December
                    17, 1962. (Memorandum for all holders of <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss>
                    6028, December 17, 1962; <persName corresp="#p_KJF2">Kennedy</persName> Library,
                    National Security Files, Countries Series, Africa)</p>
            </div>
